Description:
OLDY BUT A GOODY!!!
Full of old time charm, this property is the ideal home or getaway.
Featuring 3 bedrooms, a spacious timber kitchen with meals area and polished timber floors, a good sized lounge room with ceiling fans, split system and wood heater, a modern family bathroom and external laundry.
An undercover verandah at the rear of the house is ideal for entertaining and the established garden houses a double shed with power and lights. To the side of the house is a single carport with roller door.
Situated in a quiet location next to the park and close to the beach, this property is within 5 mins of local services, shops, cafes and wineries.

Description:
Under Contract
This fabulous 3 bedroom home is set on a 1000m2 block and is ready for you to move straight in.
The property boasts 3 bedrooms 2 with built in robes, master with ensuite, walk in robe and ceiling fan, open plan dining kitchen and family room with a slate floor, a separate living area, laundry, family bathroom and toilet, heating and cooling system.
The family room leads onto the sun-bathed covered alfresco area which is the ideal location for a lazy Sunday afternoon or to entertain guests in style. Steps lead down into the mature garden where there is plenty of room for kids to play footy.
There is a double garage 6 x 7.5 m and side gated access offering plenty of space for a caravan or boat
This property has so much to offer don't miss this opportunity!

Description:
10 Acres with 3 Bedroom Home Adjoins the Bay
This 10 acre lifestyle property has been set up with a central lane way and 10 paddocks to run mostly horses and a few other stock. The 3 bedroom home is built well back from the Bass Highway with an attractive garden and plenty of shedding. The home has a wood heater to keep you warm and a front verandah to relax on!.
The farm facilities are a 4 bay machinery shed 22m x 6m, a 9m x 6m fully enclosed shed, several other smaller sheds including one used as a hen house.
The property directly adjoins the foreshore to Westernport Bay and it is a pretty view looking over a few mangroves to see the sunset over the water and listen to the lapping of the sea onto a small beach.
Future subdivision potential STCA. Property has a good bore and town water.

VERSATILE - EQUINE TRANSPORT MARKET GARDEN - LIFESTYLE - 36 ACRES.
36 acres of real privacy, neat and tidy on the edge of town. This is an excellent property to set up a horse farm or small farm enterprises like alpacas, goat farming or market garden. With excellent lock-up shedding c/w power water and concreted floors it is a truly versatile property. Large hard stand area makes it suitable for a transport, tradesman, gardening etc.
The western red cedar home has been renovated throughout, has a huge chef kitchen.
Main features include:
- location just over an hour to CBD, on edge of township, close to racing centres,
- 36 acres pastured, well fenced, steel security gates, S&D bore, water to paddocks,
- suit market garden including organic, elevated, strong sandy soil, water available,
- excellent secure sheds include - 22Mx12M concrete, power, water, mechanics pit, office,
17Mx5M, w/shop, garage, conc. power and water 12.5Mx12.5M open machinery/hay shed, water, power,
- 3 BR WR cedar home , fully renovated, spa ensuite, 2 Bathrooms, outdoor BBQ area,
- separate fully self-contained residential unit, BIR, kitchen, laundry, carport etc
For further information or inspections please contact: RAY CULLEN on mobile: 0429 977313

Description:
COSY IMMACULATE HOME IN THE HEART OF CORINELLA COMMUNITY
Set within a scenic coastal village, this charming property with bay views
has a comfortable & spacious open plan kitchen, living and dining area
with high ceilings and floating floors throughout. Featuring 3 bedrooms
all with BIR’s, main bedroom with wall to wall carpet .The property has a
reverse cycle heating/cooling system & ceiling fans.
The generous main bathroom has a separate bath, shower and toilet.
There is also a separate laundry.
The home offers a great size deck for all your entertaining needs, along
with a utility/store room that has its own little powder room fantastic
when you’re on the deck or just doing a little gardening, no trip indoors!
This property is a must see if you are looking for a relaxed coastal
lifestyle that offers a low maintenance garden, great fishing, close
proximity to the foreshore, walking tracks, and only 90 minutes from
Melbourne CBD!
Great family home, holiday home or dynamic investment property.
A sea change worth a look. Agent available 7 days a week.

Description:
PRESENTED TO PERFECTION!!!!
CAPTURING FABULOUS BAY VIEWS!!! Set on approximately 886 sq. m. foreshore block, this immaculate, recently renovated seaside home is sure to delight with contemporary, open plan living overlooking the expanses of Westernport Bay. Upon driving up to the property it oozes a charming warm feel with an established, low maintenance garden and driveway leading to a high roofed double carport and double garage, which can house a boat. However, this property is best appreciated once inside. The house features abundant natural light, polished floorboards and reverse cycle air conditioning. It comprises a spacious living/meals area including modern stone kitchen and doors leading onto a broad timber deck, overlooking the bay. There are 3 good sized bedrooms, master having an ensuite and walk in robe. Both other bedrooms have BIR'S plus ceiling fans. There is a second living area/games room towards the back of the house, family bathroom and a good sized laundry. A laneway at the rear of the property is handy for extra access. Only a short distance to the boat ramp, but remains tranquil when the ramp is at its busiest. Walking distance to local shop, tennis courts, lawn bowls, community centre and V-line bus stops close by. Phillip Island is approximately 20 minutes away. Description:
AN IDYLLIC SEASIDE ESCAPE WITH GREAT BAY VIEWS !!
On offer is this 2 storey solidly constructed steel framed dwelling in the exclusive Settlement Point Estate of Corinella with views of Westernport Bay and French Island. Featuring -
Downstairs :
- Good size formal lounge with split-system air-conditioner and WWC
- Double bedroom with BIRs and WWC
- Bathroom
- Laundry with access to backyard
- Separate toilet
- Internal access to double garage which has kitchen facilities / ideal for fisherman
Upstairs :
- Spacious open plan kitchen with views to Corinella pier/meals and living area with impressive bay views
- Sliding door to balcony wide enough for table and chairs
- Polished timber floors
- Split-system air-conditioner
- 3 good size bedrooms all with b/i/r/s

Downstairs is a cosy kitchen, lounge room with a fan forced gas wood fire and mantle piece surround, split system air con and sliding door to front verandah. There is also a 3rd bedroom, laundry and bathroom combined.
Outside is a great undercover bbq/entertainment area with a small studio nestled in an established garden offering many fruit trees. Single garage. The property is fully fenced and is walking distance to a great park, beach, VLine and school bus services. Approx 5 minutes to local wineries and local shops with cafes, approx 40 minutes to Cranbourne. This property has a lot to offer. Inspect Now!!!!

Description:
ONLY 2 HOUSE BLOCKS FROM FORESHORE !!!
Very appealing 1 bedroom cottage situated on large block with bay and rural views. Featuring light timber walls and ceilings, cosy living area with wood heater and sliding door to deck, floor boards, country style kitchen, family bathroom with cedar feature wall, master bedroom offering beautiful bay and rural views, also with sliding door out to deck area, computer/office room.
There is a double garage with concrete floor and power and the laundry is also in garage. The cottage is built at the rear of the property to take full advantage of the views. Currently rented for $170 per week with longstanding tenant. This is an ideal property either for weekender, or in the future build a new home, as vacant blocks with these views are hard to come by.
Only minutes to 24 hour boat ramp and jetty, local primary school and kindergarten approximately 4 mins away and major shopping centre and Phillip Island approximately 25 minutes away. Tenby Point has one road to directly to the foreshore with large blocks with native settings.

Designed and built to the highest standard, this impressive 13 year old residence offers an unsurpassed Bass Coast lifestyle opportunity and is perfect for the family who must have it all, with the opportunity underneath the home to develop two more bedrooms or a Movie room - Or even a teenage retreat, that already has installed a sink and toilet.

? Galley style kitchen

? Parking with two entrances to property for boat – caravan
? Great walking tracks & a very short walk to foreshore
Don’t delay as this beach-side gem is priced to sell. Agent available 7 days a week.

Address: 128 Grantville Glen Alvie Road Grantville VIC 3984
Description:
Prime entry level home in a peaceful location.
Tucked away from the road in a quiet neighbourhood, this three-bedroom home on 564m2 (approx.) is just one minute away from the Grantville shopping precinct and presents a fantastic opportunity to enter the property market. With glimpses of the bay from the bedroom, one could easily imagine the magnificent views from an additional level or you may prefer to enjoy the home just as it is.
Light and homely, this charming property features three bedrooms with wall to wall carpets, two of which have built in robes. The master bedroom has a separate entry to the verandah with glass sliding doors to allow fresh air to circulate on those warm summer nights. The spacious open plan living/dining/kitchen is a welcoming space for friends and family to gather and other features include a central bathroom with bath, large laundry, separate toilet, linen closet and inverter split system. Outside is a carport with plenty of additional off road parking and a large backyard.
Offering so much potential in an area famous for its fishing, boating, wineries and epicurean delights, this home is also central to coastal and bushland reserves while being only 1:20hr away from Melbourne. Within half an hour in the other direction, you'll reach Phillip Island or enjoy a scenic drive along the Bass Coast. There is so much to see and do in this beautiful part of the world.
Offering
• Open plan living, dining and spacious kitchen
• Three carpeted bedrooms, two with built in robes
• Master bedroom with its own separate entry
• Inverter split system heating/cooling
• Carport with additional off road parking
• Large backyard, paved area with seating
